  "text": "where we regard f (x) = −∞ for all x ∈ R m if I = ∅. Different polynomial expressions may define the same piece-wise linear function [13, §1] . In general, it is difficult to check if two tropical polynomials define the same function [CITATION_1] . When f and g each have trivial coefficients (meaning c a = 0 for all a ∈ I and d a = 0 for all a ∈ I ), the following lemma reduces this task to a convex hull computation [13, §1] .",
